<div id="review_1255781191" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1255781191" />
    <a title="Winter" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3332159-winter"><img alt="Winter" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1433164814p2/3332159.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1255781191?book_show_action=true">Apr 15, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Winter" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Winter" href="/user/show/3332159-winter">Winter</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9789129408652" href="/book/show/10094024-br-derna-lejonhj-rta">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3332159-winter?shelf=2016-read">2016-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3332159-winter?shelf=absolute-all-time-favorites">absolute-all-time-favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3332159-winter?shelf=2019-read">2019-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1255781191" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18297514980143832295">This book is everything lovely about childhood to me. Just picking it up and looking at that well read cover and seeing the handwriting of my eight year self, I knew this was going to be as good today as then. Even though I know the story by heart, and I have seen the series/movie a ton of times, it still has something fresh and still timeless over it. <br/><br/>At least in our part of the world Astrid Lindgren is cherished and loved for her childrens’ books. She’s mostly known for Pippi Longstocking, but</span>
  <span id="freeText18297514980143832295" style="display:none">This book is everything lovely about childhood to me. Just picking it up and looking at that well read cover and seeing the handwriting of my eight year self, I knew this was going to be as good today as then. Even though I know the story by heart, and I have seen the series/movie a ton of times, it still has something fresh and still timeless over it. <br /><br />At least in our part of the world Astrid Lindgren is cherished and loved for her childrens’ books. She’s mostly known for Pippi Longstocking, but I happen to think that this one is her best. It is like a fairytale and at the same time it is also so relevant for all ages. We all have to deal with loosing someone at some point in our life.<br /><br />This book tell the tale of two brothers each brave in their own way. It is a story of loss, grief and courage. It is a story of love between the closest of siblings and a love that endures no matter the circumstances. Maybe that is why I love it so much.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18297514980143832295" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
