<div id="review_777252432" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/777252432" />
    <a title="Rebekah Waldorff" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19683573-rebekah-waldorff"><img alt="Rebekah Waldorff" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1438727492p2/19683573.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/777252432?book_show_action=true">Nov 30, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rebekah Waldorff" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rebekah Waldorff" href="/user/show/19683573-rebekah-waldorff">Rebekah Waldorff</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer777252432" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11531534032602679437">It has been a while since I&apos;ve read this book. But it still deserves a review from me. The writing style is gripping and the characters endearing. The message of familial love is well writ and heart wrenching. Now, that was the good part. I warn you that there will be a spoiler, and a scathing review next, because no reader should venture into this book unwarned and I suggest you look closely at this book before passing it onto a child: <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[The main characters are both brothers. After</span></span>
  <span id="freeText11531534032602679437" style="display:none">It has been a while since I've read this book. But it still deserves a review from me. The writing style is gripping and the characters endearing. The message of familial love is well writ and heart wrenching. Now, that was the good part. I warn you that there will be a spoiler, and a scathing review next, because no reader should venture into this book unwarned and I suggest you look closely at this book before passing it onto a child: <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[The main characters are both brothers. After they die, they both go to a fantasy land, where they have a wonderful adventure and then--now that one of them is crippled--decide to go on to 'the next land.' So they both jump off of a cliff! Although the familial love in this book is refreshing, the heavy undertones of suicide are not. Beware of this book for children, only adults who can handle this subject and reason well should venture into this read. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span></span>
