<div id="review_2094842595" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2094842595" />
    <a title="Irene" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4713275-irene"><img alt="Irene" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1368817150p2/4713275.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2094842595?book_show_action=true">Aug 17, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Irene" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Irene" href="/user/show/4713275-irene">Irene</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9788251792455" href="/book/show/1772374.Br_drene_L_vehjerte">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4713275-irene?shelf=danish">danish</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4713275-irene?shelf=from-library">from-library</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4713275-irene?shelf=2017">2017</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2094842595" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4739196935649296638">I remember my mom reading this to me when I was very young. It&apos;s just as good as I remembered it to be.<br/><br/>I love the way Karl describes his brother Jonathan, it&apos;s full of admiration and love, in a way only a child can describe it.<br/>I also really loved grandpa and the way he tested these two young boys. He was easily my favourite character.<br/><br/>The setting of Nangijala was perfect and romantic, and i cam understand why Karl wanted to go there.<br/><br/>The white doves were a nice touch and very symbolic. <br/><br/>I remembere</span>
  <span id="freeText4739196935649296638" style="display:none">I remember my mom reading this to me when I was very young. It's just as good as I remembered it to be.<br /><br />I love the way Karl describes his brother Jonathan, it's full of admiration and love, in a way only a child can describe it.<br />I also really loved grandpa and the way he tested these two young boys. He was easily my favourite character.<br /><br />The setting of Nangijala was perfect and romantic, and i cam understand why Karl wanted to go there.<br /><br />The white doves were a nice touch and very symbolic. <br /><br />I remembered it being much more sad, and so I was surprised when I found out that this wasn't necessarily a story about loss, but more so one of courage and love.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4739196935649296638" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


