<span id="freeTextContainer11604882928315129752"><b> 5 Stars - I laugh, I sob, I love and I enjoy…<br/><br/>A great children&apos;s book; <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6875328.The_Brothers_Lionheart' title='The Brothers Lionheart by Astrid Lindgren' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Brothers Lionheart</a>.</b><br/>I remember when my school teacher read a chapter from this beautiful book for us every morning. I remember when my mother read it for my little brother. Later I watch the Swedish movie, I read the book myself and as adult listened to it as a radio serial some year ago. Written by our Swedish pride, the admired author of so many loved children&apos;s books <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/410653.Astrid_Lindgren' title='Astrid Lindgren' rel='nofollow noopener'>Astrid Lindgren</a>. — This time I listened to an audiobo</span>
  <span id="freeText11604882928315129752" style="display:none"><b> 5 Stars - I laugh, I sob, I love and I enjoy…<br /><br />A great children's book; <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6875328.The_Brothers_Lionheart" title="The Brothers Lionheart by Astrid Lindgren" rel="nofollow noopener">The Brothers Lionheart</a>.</b><br />I remember when my school teacher read a chapter from this beautiful book for us every morning. I remember when my mother read it for my little brother. Later I watch the Swedish movie, I read the book myself and as adult listened to it as a radio serial some year ago. Written by our Swedish pride, the admired author of so many loved children's books <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/410653.Astrid_Lindgren" title="Astrid Lindgren" rel="nofollow noopener">Astrid Lindgren</a>. — This time I listened to an audiobook edition narrated by the author herself in the 70's.<br /><br />Just as sad and emotional as wonderful. A beautiful story for children … and grownups.<br /><br />**************************<br /><br /><a href="https://www.astridlindgren.com/en/characters/the-brothers-lionheart" rel="nofollow noopener">Astrid about the story/tale and characters</a> <br /><a href="https://www.astridlindgren.com/sv/karaktarerna/broderna-lejonhjarta/historien-bakom-broderna-lejonhjarta" rel="nofollow noopener">Astrid om sagan och karaktärerna</a><br /><br /><i>"The Brothers Lionheart is a tale of love strong enough to conquer death – not just once, but twice. After brothers Jonathan and Crusty (Skorpan) pass away they meet again in Nangijala, the land of eternal spring. Casting a long shadow over their world is the evil tyrant Tengil, ruler of the country Karmanjaka, where he’s building his new fortress up in the The Ancient Mountains.<br /><br />It’s a tale about the battle between good and evil, between fear and courage, about a struggle for freedom – and about death. </i><br /><br />**************************<br /><br />Wow!! I didn’t remember it was such a grand book. — So very touching and heartwarmingly told. Horrors such as death, dragons, traitors and evil soldiers but with so much imagination, and heroism … and it is always a child who become strong and who end as the true hero. — Everything told in the very best Astrid Lindgren way. — She was just the best. Her books and characters are unforgettable. <br /><br />I LIKE - I LOVE ❣️<br /><br />Read February 1, 2022</span>
