<div id="review_688839453" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/688839453" />
    <a title="Anna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21861695-anna"><img alt="Anna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1395578341p2/21861695.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/688839453?book_show_action=true">Aug 07, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anna" href="/user/show/21861695-anna">Anna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21861695-anna?shelf=absolute-favourites">absolute-favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21861695-anna?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21861695-anna?shelf=horses">horses</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer688839453" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17441311001549725529">I love this book more than any other Lindgren. It helped me with my fear of death as a child like nothing else possibly could have done. I read it over and over again and am now reading it to my youngest who is currently struggling with all those dark fear after her best friend&apos;s mother died suddenly a few weeks ago. To me this is the book Lindgren should have been famous for. It is one of the most beautiful and profound adventure stories for young children ever written.</span>
  <span id="freeText17441311001549725529" style="display:none">I love this book more than any other Lindgren. It helped me with my fear of death as a child like nothing else possibly could have done. I read it over and over again and am now reading it to my youngest who is currently struggling with all those dark fear after her best friend's mother died suddenly a few weeks ago. To me this is the book Lindgren should have been famous for. It is one of the most beautiful and profound adventure stories for young children ever written.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17441311001549725529" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


